<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-10-03T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-10-03T16:00:00-05:00" n="336" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d336">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 Naval Armaments/135:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The American Delegate to the Bureau of the General
                                Disarmament Conference (<persName corresp="#p_WHR1" type="from">Wilson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-10-03T22:00:00+01:00">October 3,
                                    1932—10 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received October 3—5:43 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>397. From <persName corresp="#p_DNH1">Davis</persName>. <persName corresp="#p_SSJ1">Simon</persName>, who must return to London
                            tomorrow stopping for a conversation with <persName corresp="#p_HE1">Herriot</persName> in Paris, has asked me to come to London the end
                            of this week to take up the naval conversations. We therefore plan to
                            leave here Thursday.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_WHR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>